news.title: Nimbus Group to invest ₹1,100 crore to revive housing project in Noida
news.para: Nimbus Group is set to invest ₹1,100 crore in Arista Luxe Phase II, a residential project in Noida's Sector 168, reviving the stalled development under the Legacy Stalled Projects Scheme. The 10-acre project, being developed through a joint development agreement, will feature 342 apartments across four towers and is slated for completion by 2029.

news.title: Builders seek hassle-free access to m-sand after Maharashtra govt finalises SOP for policy
news.para: Maharashtra builders are advocating for streamlined access and transportation of manufactured sand (M Sand) following the finalization of the M Sand policy SOP, aimed at eliminating river sand mining. Developers emphasize the need for quick permissions, reliable supply chains, and improved rural infrastructure to ensure the policy's success.

news.title: Lucknow: LDA plans raising development charges for properties near expressways
news.para: The Lucknow Development Authority (LDA) is set to increase development charges for properties near key corridors and expressways. Upcoming meeting will address infrastructure improvements, housing scheme budgets including Anantnagar and IT City, and conversion of flats.

news.title: Cochin development body to pool 1,000 acres for Infopark Phase III
news.para: Greater Cochin Development Authority has started land pooling for Infopark's Phase III. The project aims to establish a new campus across 300 acres in Kizhakkambalam and Kunnathunadu. This will be Kerala's first land-pooling project. GCDA will publish a notification and consult landowners. The campus will feature carbon neutrality, water self-sufficiency, and complete waste management.

news.title: Maharashtra CM pushes for housing development near metro corridor terminals
news.para: Chief Minister Devendra Fadnavis has urged for housing developments near Metro terminals to optimize land use and improve connectivity. He emphasized the importance of completing projects within three years and addressing delays promptly. Fadnavis also mandated that project updates be reported on the CM Dashboard for efficient monitoring and resolution.

news.title: NBFCs nudge RBI for lower risk weight on loans against property
news.para: In their discussions with the Reserve Bank of India (RBI), non-banking financial companies have requested LAPs be not treated on a par with unsecured loans when assigning risk weights. They have urged the RBI to reduce the current cap of 125% and align more closely with home loans, which attract risk weights in the range of 35% to 50%.

news.title: Kerala unveils first neurodiversity-friendly co-working hub at Kochi metro station
news.para: Kerala has launched its first neurodiversity-friendly coworking space, 'i by Infopark,' at Ernakulam South Metro Station. The 48,000 sq ft facility can accommodate over 550 professionals and offers flexible workspaces with modern amenities. Chief Minister Pinarayi Vijayan envisions this project as a model for future expansion across the state, aiming to boost innovation and job creation.

news.title: Building products maker HNI to acquire Steelcase for $2.2 billion
news.para: HNI has agreed to acquire Steelcase, a major office furniture manufacturer, in a deal valued at approximately $2.2 billion, consisting of both cash and stock. This strategic move aims to capitalize on the increasing trend of companies requiring employees to return to the office.

news.title: Ghaziabad: 20 years on, GDA may file FIR against officials for 134 extra flats in society
news.para: Ghaziabad Development Authority (GDA) is set to take strict action against officials involved in allowing a private developer to construct 134 unauthorized flats at Express Garden society in Indirapuram. A GDA panel, formed following a High Court directive, will submit its report recommending FIRs against the architect, developer, and implicated GDA officials.

news.title: India office market set to cross one billion sq ft of office stock: Report
news.para: India's office market is poised to surpass one billion sq ft by Q3 2025, marking substantial growth at a CAGR of 8.6% over two decades. Bengaluru leads with 23% of the total stock, followed by NCR and Mumbai.

news.title: Haryana to roll out pilot initiative for online paperless deed registration
news.para: The Haryana government is launching a pilot project for an online, paperless deed registration system in Naraingarh tehsil, starting August 11. This initiative aims to simplify land registration, reduce public interaction, and enhance transparency. The system allows online appointments, document verification, and real-time updates of revenue records, ultimately streamlining the process and minimizing inefficiencies.

news.title: Singapore's CapitaLand Integrated to acquire remaining 55% stake in Glory Office Trust
news.para: CapitaLand Integrated Commercial Trust (CICT) is set to acquire the remaining 55% stake in Glory Office Trust for S$1.05 billion. This acquisition includes the office and retail components of CapitaSpring in Singapore, with CapitaLand Development and Mitsubishi Estate divesting their stakes. CICT plans to fund the acquisition through a private placement, aiming to raise approximately S$500 million.

news.title: Delhi HC denies bail to DHFL's promoter in ₹34,926 crore bank fraud case
news.para: Kapil Wadhawan's bail plea got rejected by the Delhi High Court. The case involves a massive bank fraud of Rs 34,926 crore. The court cited Wadhawan's conduct during custody as a reason. Allegations include manipulation of assets and transactions. The court fears he might tamper with evidence or flee. He faces multiple investigations across jurisdictions.

news.title: Carlyle raises $9 billion for US real estate bets
news.para: Carlyle Group successfully raised $9 billion for its U.S. real estate fund, exceeding its predecessor's $8 billion despite a challenging fundraising environment. The fund will strategically invest in residential, self-storage, and industrial sectors, avoiding office, hotels, and traditional retail. Carlyle aims to capitalize on improving fundamentals and reduced liquidity in these target areas.

news.title: Knowledge Realty Trust REIT raises ₹1,620 crore from anchor investors
news.para: Knowledge Realty Trust REIT secured significant funding before its IPO. It raised ₹1,620 crore from anchor investors. An additional ₹1,200 crore came via strategic allocation. The IPO opens for public subscription on August 5, 2025. 70% of the IPO is already committed. Proceeds will repay debts and for corporate purposes.

news.title: Nagpur civic body puts tax defaulters’ property under hammer, but only 106 of 4.6 lakh face action
news.para: The Nagpur Municipal Corporation (NMC) faces a significant challenge with property tax arrears reaching Rs938.7 crore, as 4.6 lakh property owners defaulted in 2024-25. Despite issuing recovery warrants and attaching properties, the NMC has initiated auction proceedings against only 106 defaulters. Experts emphasize the need for systemic reforms, improved data management, and stricter enforcement to address the growing financial strain.

news.title: Minister announces dedicated township for Ambedkar Layout residents in Mysuru
news.para: Social welfare minister HC Mahadevappa announced the identification of 20 acres for a dedicated township to address housing challenges for Ambedkar Layout residents in Ashokapuram. Consultations are underway with officials to locate suitable land, reflecting Chief Minister Siddaramaiah's commitment to Ashokapuram's development. Additionally, funds have been allocated for community hall renovation and completing Ambedkar Bhavan.

news.title: Aamir Khan rents four apartments in Mumbai’s Pali Hill
news.para: Aamir Khan has secured a five-year lease for four luxury apartments in Mumbai's Pali Hill, costing Rs 24.5 lakh monthly with a Rs 1.47 crore deposit. The agreement includes a 5% annual rent increase and a 45-month lock-in period. This move coincides with the redevelopment plans for Khan's current residence, where he owns multiple apartments.

news.title: No poor family in Haryana will remain homeless: CM
news.para: Chief Minister Nayab Singh Saini affirmed Haryana's commitment to eliminating homelessness, distributing ownership certificates and plot allotment letters to beneficiaries under the Mukhyamantri Shehri Awas Yojana and Gramin Awas Yojana 2.0. The government is providing financial assistance for house construction, ensuring transparent beneficiary selection, and coordinating with the central government to achieve housing goals.

news.title: Real estate rebounds with a new talent playbook: Pay, performance and parity
news.para: India's real estate sector is undergoing a significant transformation, prioritizing talent and inclusion. Compensation trends reveal substantial growth, especially in leadership roles and performance-based pay. The industry is witnessing increased demand for specialized functions and a notable rise in gender diversity, signaling a strategic shift towards a more equitable and results-oriented future.
